<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-435-443  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 435 443.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  Sept 17 1990 n386 p82(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>System 7.0 ready to deliver. (Apple Computer Inc.'s Macintoshoperating system) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gore, Andrew.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Apple is scheduled to introduce the System 7.0 operating systemfor Macintosh microcomputers in Jan 1991.andP;  The new version isdesigned as a true 32-bit operating environment, like OS/2, andincludes such high-end features as virtual memory, InterApplication Communication (IAC) and built-in peer-to-peer filesharing.andP;  The software will retain the Macintosh desktop interfaceand will be compatible with most existing software and Macintoshcomputers, unlike OS/2, which is a considerable departure fromMS-DOS in terms of interface and compatibility.andP;  Eight key System7.0 enhancements are described: the Additions Manager, AppleEvents, Help Manager, Data Access Manager, TrueType outline fontstandard and manager, Virtual Memory, New Finder and Font/DAMover.andP;  Peer-to-peer file sharing is also supported in the newsoftware.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Apple Computer Inc. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    AAPL.andO;Product:   System 7.0 (Operating system) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Operating SystemsEnhancements32-BitProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>